<dl id="s17019bj"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="us17" href="#s17019bj">Ithaca: </a><a href="../../ff/unbs/s17all.htm#s17019bj">sector 19(bj)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> atom</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Each element is assumed to consist of indivisible particles called <mark>atoms</mark>. The atoms of the same element have the same weight, but the atoms of different elements have different weights. Every chemical change is a re-arrangement of atoms. When one or more atoms of one element unite with one or more atoms of another element, a molecule of a new substance is formed. <small> Wentworth and Hill, <a name="TBOP" href="/udra/udex.htm#tbop"><cite title="source">A Text-Book of Physics</cite></a> (1904), 167</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
